text: Imst is a town in the Austrian state of Tyrol. It is the capital of the district of Imst. As of 1 January 2019, 10,628 people lived there. It is on the river Inn in western Tyrol, and is about west of Innsbruck. == References == == Other websites == * Official Homepage of the town of Imst Category:Settlements in Tyrol (state)
